---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const expertise = [
  'Engineering Leadership',
  'Front-End Engineering',
  'Team Dynamics & Culture',
  'AI & Emerging Tech',
  'Product & UX',
  'Business–Engineering Translation',
];
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="Once an engineer, always an engineer. I traded creating software for creating solutions, and the teams that build them."
>
  <!-- ── PAGE HEADER ──────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container page-header__inner">
      <span class="label">About</span>
      <h1 class="page-header__title">
        Once an engineer, always an engineer.<br />
        <span class="accent">I traded code for the teams that write it.</span>
      </h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── BIO ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="bio-heading">
    <div class="container about-grid">
      <div class="about-body">
        <div class="divider--orange" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;"></div>

        <p class="about-lead">
          It's hard to put a traditional label on the roles I've played. Most of my time writing code was as a front-end engineer, but I bounced around back-end, devops, UX and product too. Wherever there was a gap, or a problem with fuzzy edges, that's where I've gone. I've often described myself, tongue firmly in-cheek, as a "full hack" developer, rather than full-stack.
        </p>

        <p class="muted">
          That didn't stop when I moved off the code and into leadership. In fact, I made that move to close a gap I kept running into. Engineering leaders who couldn't give business context to engineers in a way they could parse, and equally couldn't advocate for engineers who needed someone who knew how to make a compelling business case.
        </p>

        <p class="muted">
          I think of myself as a swiss army knife. I know enough, about enough, that I know what's needed and can paper over gaps in the short term.
        </p>

        <p class="muted">
          I write about two things: people and emerging tech (right now, that means AI). Particularly, I write about how those two things mix, or don't as the case may be.
        </p>

        <blockquote>
          "I write to share ideas worth thinking about, and to give people language for things they already know but haven't said yet."
        </blockquote>

        <p class="muted">
          Based in Melbourne, Australia. Outside of work I'm fortunate to have a family to love and be loved by. I spend my free time out on the golf course (mostly the trees), or deep in a book or video game.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="about-sidebar">
        <!-- Expertise -->
        <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);">
          <span class="label" style="margin-bottom: 1rem; display: block;">Domain Expertise</span>
          <ul class="expertise-list">
            {expertise.map(item => (
              <li class="expertise-item">
                <span class="expertise-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                <span>{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Current focus -->
        <div class="card">
          <span class="label" style="margin-bottom: 1rem; display: block;">Currently</span>
          <p class="muted" style="font-size: var(--t-sm);">
            Writing about the people side of engineering and the pragmatics of AI. Based in Melbourne, Australia.
          </p>
          <a href="mailto:jesse@jessegreen.tech" class="btn btn--primary" style="margin-top: 1.5rem; width: 100%; justify-content: center;">
            Get in touch
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── PHILOSOPHY STRIP ──────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section--tight philosophy" aria-label="Leadership philosophy">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="philosophy__grid">
        <div class="philosophy__item">
          <span class="philosophy__num">01</span>
          <h4>Full hack, not full-stack</h4>
          <p class="muted" style="font-size: var(--t-sm);">
            Most gaps aren't front-end or back-end problems. They're fuzzy-edged, cross-discipline problems. That's where I've always gone.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="philosophy__item">
          <span class="philosophy__num">02</span>
          <h4>Teams are people, not output</h4>
          <p class="muted" style="font-size: var(--t-sm);">
            Engineers aren't black boxes where input equals output. Understanding what drives behaviour and engagement is the difference between a team that ships and one that stalls.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="philosophy__item">
          <span class="philosophy__num">03</span>
          <h4>No hype. No fear.</h4>
          <p class="muted" style="font-size: var(--t-sm);">
            On AI and emerging tech, find what's useful, stay skeptical where needed, and know how to tell the difference. I understand the technology and lead the people building with it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── CTA ───────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section--tight" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--c-border);">
    <div class="container" style="display: flex; gap: var(--sp-4); flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <a href="/cv" class="btn btn--primary">View full CV</a>
      <a href="/writing" class="btn btn--ghost">Read the thinking</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
.accent { color: var(--c-accent); }

.page-header {
  padding-top: calc(var(--nav-h) + var(--sp-16));
  padding-bottom: var(--sp-16);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-border);
  background: var(--c-surface);
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.page-header::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  bottom: -40%;
  right: -5%;
  width: 400px;
  height: 400px;
  background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(255,85,0,0.05) 0%, transparent 70%);
  pointer-events: none;
}

.page-header__title {
  margin-top: var(--sp-4);
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);
  max-width: 18ch;
}

.about-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 340px;
  gap: var(--sp-16);
  align-items: start;
}

.about-lead {
  font-size: var(--t-xl);
  font-weight: 500;
  line-height: 1.5;
  color: var(--c-text);
  margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);
  max-width: 56ch;
}

.expertise-list {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--sp-3);
}

.expertise-item {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--sp-3);
  font-family: var(--f-accent);
  font-size: var(--t-sm);
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--c-text-muted);
}

.expertise-dot {
  width: 6px;
  height: 6px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: var(--c-accent);
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.philosophy {
  background: var(--c-surface);
  border-top: 1px solid var(--c-border);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-border);
}

.philosophy__grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: var(--sp-8);
}

.philosophy__num {
  font-family: var(--f-accent);
  font-size: var(--t-xs);
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: var(--c-accent);
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
}

.philosophy__item h4 {
  font-size: var(--t-base);
  font-weight: 700;
  margin-bottom: var(--sp-3);
}

@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .about-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .about-sidebar { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--sp-6); }
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .philosophy__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .about-sidebar { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
</style>
